DESCRIPTION OF MALE (
holotype
): Colour (in alcohol) generally brown, carapace, chelicerae and ventral sclerites dark brown; membranous parts of opisthosoma light grey-brown. “Thoracic” portion of carapace unusually narrow in dorsal view. Clypeus without median process (Fig. 18A). Fovea deepened and slightly widened in anterior portion. Total length 6.7. Carapace 3.5 long, 2.1 wide. Eye sizes and interdistances: PME 0.21 long, separated by 0.24; ALE 0.22 long; ALE-PLE 0.06; PLE 0.22 long, separated by 1.07. Labium 0.6 long, 0.8 wide. Sternum 2.2 long, 1.5 wide. Chelicerae without modifications; with two teeth on anterior margin of fang furrow.
